This method updates the status within `self._module_msgs_state`. It first uses an assertion to ensure the provided line is positive before attempting to update the internal storage.

```python
def set_msg_status(self, msg, line, status):
        """Set status (enabled/disable) for a given message at a given line"""
        assert line > 0
        try:
            self._module_msgs_state[msg.msgid][line] = status
        except KeyError:
            self._module_msgs_state[msg.msgid] = {line: status}
```

The use of try/except gracefully handles cases where a message ID has never been seen before, initializing its entry with just that single status.
